      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "All three FEA codes (FDA in-house, Ansys 2022 R2, DePuy Synthes internal solver) operate under documented software quality management systems with version control, regression test suites, and release qualification records. Achieved level 3 satisfies required level 2 for this factor."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Each solver in the ensemble has been verified against NAFEMS benchmark problems relevant to structural contact and large-displacement bending. Patch test and manufactured-solution checks confirm correct implementation of the constitutive routines used for titanium alloy. Achieved level 3 satisfies required level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study must demonstrate QoI change less than 2% between penultimate and final refinement levels.",
      "rationale": "A systematic h-refinement study was performed on the screw–rod–vertebral body interface region. Stiffness and yield load QoIs changed by less than 1.4% between the medium and fine meshes (element edge length 0.3 mm vs. 0.15 mm at critical cross-section). Richardson extrapolation confirms GCI below 2%. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual convergence criteria and energy balance checks documented and within solver tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solver residuals converged to below 1e-5 relative norm for all load steps. Energy balance error remained below 0.5% across the full displacement ramp. Iterative solver (PCG with incomplete Cholesky preconditioner) tolerance set to 1e-8. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation execution checklist completed and independently reviewed by a second analyst.",
      "rationale": "A documented simulation execution protocol was followed by each participating organization. An independent senior analyst reviewed boundary condition assignments, material property inputs, and contact definitions prior to each production run. No use errors were identified during review. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form assumptions justified by literature or sensitivity analysis; key simplifications documented.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V, E=114 GPa, nu=0.34) is justified for the sub-yield regime; bilinear isotropic hardening is activated for post-yield response. Bone-analog block modeled as rigid per ASTM F1717 fixture specification. Screw–rod interface modeled with frictional contact (mu=0.2), consistent with published cadaveric and in vitro data. Sensitivity analysis confirmed model form contribution to QoI uncertainty is below 5%. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric inputs traceable to certified measurements or published standards.",
      "rationale": "Screw geometry digitized from coordinate measuring machine (CMM) data with 5-micron accuracy. Material properties sourced from ASTM F136 certificate of conformance for the specific lot used in the experimental constructs. Rod diameter and modulus verified against manufacturer datasheet and independent tensile coupon testing (N=3). Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (1000 samples); 95th-percentile QoI spread within 3.8%. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sample size and lot traceability sufficient to characterize inter-specimen variability.",
      "rationale": "N=11 experimental constructs assembled from a single manufacturing lot of non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screws and 5.5 mm titanium rods. All specimens inspected with CMM prior to testing; dimensional variation documented. Inter-specimen coefficient of variation for stiffness was 3.2%, consistent with manufacturing tolerances. Sample size provides 80% power to detect a 10% mean shift at alpha=0.05. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of loading scenarios relevant to the intended use.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single quasi-static compression-bending condition per ASTM F1717 (10 mm/min crosshead displacement, ambient temperature, dry). No cyclic fatigue or off-axis loading conditions were evaluated. This single test condition limits the breadth of validation coverage and is the one factor below required level. The shortfall is acknowledged in the decision record; the model is not used to predict fatigue or multi-axial loading response within this COU."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA inputs demonstrably equivalent to experimental specimen and fixture parameters.",
      "rationale": "FEA boundary conditions replicate the ASTM F1717 fixture geometry including block spacing (100 mm), loading point offset, and constraint conditions. Material inputs matched to lot-specific coupon data. Screw insertion angle (0 degrees, straight) confirmed identical between FEA and all 11 physical specimens. Equivalency confirmed by blinded comparison of FEA setup parameters against test records by an independent reviewer. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., ASME V&V 20 validation metric or equivalent) applied; FEA predictions within acceptance band.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness and 0.2%-offset yield load compared using the area validation metric (AVM) per ASME V&V 20. FEA ensemble mean stiffness: 412 N/mm (experimental mean: 408 N/mm, SD 13 N/mm). FEA ensemble mean yield load: 1,847 N (experimental mean: 1,831 N, SD 58 N). AVM score 0.94 for stiffness, 0.91 for yield load, both exceeding the 0.85 acceptance threshold. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to the clinical and regulatory decision question.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load under ASTM F1717 compression-bending are the primary mechanical performance endpoints cited in the 510(k) predicate comparison and in FDA guidance on spinal fixation systems. These QoIs are directly relevant to the regulatory decision. No surrogate or proxy QoIs are used. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activity geometry, materials, loading, and boundary conditions sufficiently representative of the COU.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity uses the identical screw design, rod system, and ASTM F1717 protocol as the intended regulatory submission test. Two independent laboratories participated, confirming cross-site reproducibility. The validation domain (non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw, quasi-static compression-bending) directly maps to the COU as described in the Claim and Requirement documentation. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    }
