    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA ensemble achieves or exceeds required credibility levels for 12 of 13 V&V 40 factors. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is bounded in scope: the model is used exclusively for quasi-static compression-bending prediction per ASTM F1717 in support of a 510(k) submission, and no extrapolation to fatigue or multi-axial loading is claimed. The output comparison metric (AVM > 0.85 for both QoIs) and cross-laboratory reproducibility provide sufficient confidence for the intended regulatory use. The assessment team accepts the package at Medium assurance level consistent with model risk level 3.",
